Notes:
- "build-workflow" is the name of the workflow
- "deploy-to-staging" and "check-code-quality" are the first two steps of the workflow, each with a "next" step
- "check-build-status" is the third step, it checks the build status of the staging environment and updates the "environment.staging" variable
- "deploy" is the final step of the workflow, it deploys the production environment to the staging environment
- The "actions" array contains the "deploy-to-staging" and "check-code-quality" steps
- The "config" array contains the "env" and "JWT_SECRET" environment variables for the "deploy" step, and the "command" for the "check-code-quality" step
- The "conditions" array contains the "environment.staging" condition for the "deploy" step, and the "environment.production" condition for the "check-code-quality" step
- The "actions" array contains the "deploy-to-staging" step, which has an "id" of "deploy", a "name" of "Deploy to Staging", and a "type" of "condition"
- The "config" array contains the "condition" for the "deploy" step and the "restart" and "environment" for the "deploy" step
- The "actions" array contains the "check-code-quality" step, which has an "id" of "check-code-quality", a "name" of "Code Quality Check", and a "type" of "loop"
